import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['wounds'], label='Wounds')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['other'], label='Other Injuries')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['disease'], label='Diseases')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Cases')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of wounds, other injuries, and diseases over time?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['wounds'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wounds?')
    plt.xlabel('Number of wounds')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
